SUITE.NAME: All tests in test: zirconium Coverage Results

task.summary: Got a simplified version of zirconium up and running. added some instructions to the readme. now im going to attempt to build the gem.
added a disclaimer to the readme file
updated the install instructions in the readme. and included the first build of the .gem file for download and testing
added .idea directory to the ignore file
overrode equals on expectations. overrode to_s on mock_objects. mock_objects will not store a list of expectations in methods_called instead of a list of symbols.
Added the ability for a mock object to find a called method by its method symbol. if none is found, an empty Expectation is returned.
Added a called_with? method to Expectation so that the user may assert a method was called with a list of arguments. Made method_valid? private on MockObject.
Fixed a bug where arguments werent properly being passed to Expectation in MockObject.method_missing

Renamed method_symbol to symbol and arguments_passed_in to arguments on Expectation. This should make tests less verbose.
Added a method(symbol, *args) method to MockObject to find an expectation that matches both the symbol and arguments. Wheras method_named only returns the first expectation that matches that symbol.
Added basic stubbing logic to allow users to stub out instance methods. It cant currently stub class methods.
